    In this recording, the Czech soprano Zdenka Zika (Zdeňka Zíková 1902-1990) sings Aida's famous aria 'O patria mia' from Verdi's opera of the same name in Slovene. She has worked in Ljubljana, Zagreb, Prague, Belgrade and Vienna. (Interesting fact - the mother's maiden name was Krainz; it is possible that her ancestors were also from Carniola.)
